div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 244px; white-space: nowrap; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

font.font: A client books an initial appointment with a practitioner.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 398px; white-space: nowrap; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

font.font: At the time of booking, the member of staff who recorded the appointment can enter the CMS, create a new file for the client and generate what in OMSSS is called a 'collection'.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 270px; white-space: nowrap; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

font.font: The CMS will use the OMSS API to request a new collection.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 398px; white-space: nowrap; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

font.font: The OMSSS will send a link or QR code to the client. When the client follows the link they will be taken to the measure for them to fill in.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 398px; white-space: nowrap; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

font.font: The client completes the measure either at home on their own device or in the waiting room prior to their appointment.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 398px; white-space: nowrap; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

font.b: Completed measure is uploaded in other systems

font.font: When the client completes the measure in OMSSS, the original CMS will be notified and can request the individual item scores for storage in its database. OMSSS can optionally email a report of the results to the psychologist.
